General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 2. Costs of financing for the production, of bonding related to the
2 production, of production-related insurance coverage obtained
3 on the production; and expenses production.
4 3. Expenses for insurance coverage purchased from a related
5 member.
6 4. For game shows and productions that document purportedly
7 unscripted real-life situations primarily using unfamiliar
8 people in lieu of professional actors, (i) costs for and value of
9 prizes awarded and (ii) the fair market value of any item in the
10 show intentionally or negligently used or destroyed for
11 entertainment purposes immediately prior to its destruction or
12 use.
13 …
14 (h) Micro-Budget Productions Account. – There is created in the Film and Entertainment
15 Grant Fund a special, nonreverting account to be known as the Micro-Budget Productions
16 Account to provide funds to encourage smaller productions to develop the filmmaking industry
17 within the State. The Department of Commerce shall adopt guidelines providing for the
18 administration of the program. Those guidelines shall apply to each grant from the account and
19 shall adhere to the provisions in this section, with the following modifications:
20 (1) The funds are reserved for a production on which the production company has
21 qualifying expenses of at least fifty thousand dollars ($50,000) in the State but
22 not more than one million four hundred ninety-nine thousand dollars
23 ($1,499,000) for the production.
24 (2) The funds are not used to provide a grant in excess of (i) a base amount equal
25 to the lesser of twenty percent (20%) of the qualifying expenses for the
26 production or one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) plus (ii) any of the
27 following:
28 a. A bonus amount equal to five percent (5%) of the base amount if the
29 production company provides qualified accounting showing at least
30 seventy-five percent (75%) of the compensation and wages paid for
31 the production was paid to North Carolina residents. For purposes of
32 this sub-subdivision, "qualified accounting" by the production
33 company includes both (i) withholding payments remitted to the
34 Department of Revenue under Article 4A of Chapter 105 of the
35 General Statutes and (ii) payments for compensation to independent
36 contractors reported using a Form 1099. In calculating whether the
37 required percentage has been met, the following shall be included in
38 compensation and wages: employee fringe contributions, including
39 health, pension, and welfare contributions; per diems, stipends, and
40 living allowances paid for work being performed in this State; and
41 payments made to a loan-out company for services provided in the
42 State.
43 b. A bonus amount equal to (i) three percent (3%) if at least seventy-five
44 percent (75%) of the filming occurred in development tier two and one
45 areas or (ii) five percent (5%) if at least seventy-five percent (75%) of
46 the filming occurred in a development tier one area. For purposes of
47 this sub-subdivision, a "development tier area" is as defined in
48 G.S. 143B-437.08.
49 (3) The funds are reserved for a production for which at least seventy-five percent
50 (75%) of the filming occurred in the State by or with a production company
51 with company headquarters, as defined in G.S. 143B-437.01, in this State.
DRS35440-MCa-324 Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (4) The funds are not contingent on the existence, proof, or guarantee of a
2 distribution agreement.
3 (5) A production is not limited to feature-length films, television series, or
4 commercials but can consist of short films, documentaries, or other similar
5 audiovisual works intended for distribution that meet the requirements of this
6 subsection.
7 (6) No grant may be awarded that, when considered together with other grants
8 awarded during a single calendar year, could cause the State's potential total
9 annual liability for grants awarded in a single calendar year to exceed the
10 amount available in the Account."
11 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
12 Commerce the sum of one million five hundred thousand dollars ($1,500,000) in nonrecurring
13 funds beginning in the 2026-2027 fiscal year to the Micro-Budget Productions Account
14 established in Section 1 of this act for purposes consistent with that Account.
15 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026, and applies to grants made on
16 or after that date.
